{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   /start-here — the orientation pathway for newcomers.

   Editorial: this page is the answer to "where do I start?" — a problem
   the site otherwise leaves to the visitor. Seven curated explorations
   sequenced as Framework → Emotion → Quantification → Introduction →
   Mechanism → Evidence (paired) → Commitment. Each step exposes its
   "framing label" so the reader sees the deliberate sequencing.

   Audience: pre-conviction Normies. Welcoming intro, explicit payoff
   per step. Applied surfaces (calculators, BvSM, etc.) deliberately
   excluded from the pathway and surfaced only in the closing
   "Now what?" block as natural next layers.

   Structure:
     - Hero (welcome + curation philosophy)
     - .sh-pathway ol with 7 steps; step 6 is paired (PL + Gallery)
     - .sh-now-what closing block (Retirement + BvRE highlighted)
     - Related cards (Gallery, Retirement, BvRE again — reciprocal)
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

<main>
  <article class="start-here-page">

    {# ─── Hero / welcome ─── #}
    <section class="sh-hero">
      <p class="sh-eyebrow">A curated path</p>
      <h1 class="sh-title">Start <em>Here</em></h1>
      <p class="sh-subtitle">For people relatively new to Bitcoin &mdash; and ready to actually understand it.</p>
      <div class="sh-intro">
        <p>There's a lot on this site, and most of it doesn't make sense in isolation. The seven explorations below are sequenced so that each one earns the next:</p>
        <p class="sh-intro-sequence"><em>framework</em> before <em>emotion</em>, <em>emotion</em> before <em>quantification</em>, <em>quantification</em> before <em>introduction</em>, then <em>mechanism</em>, <em>evidence</em>, and finally <em>commitment</em>.</p>
        <p>By the time you reach the seventh, you'll understand the structural case for Bitcoin more clearly than most people who hold it &mdash; and more clearly than nearly everyone in your peer group. No prior knowledge required. Each step is short.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# ─── The pathway: 7 steps ─── #}
    <ol class="sh-pathway">

      {# Step 1 — Framework #}
      <li class="sh-step" data-step="1">
