            <h2 class="sh-step-title">What Money Has To Be</h2>
          </a>
          <p class="sh-step-desc">The irreducible trilemma. One money must <em>store value</em> across time, <em>move value</em> across space, and serve as a <em>unit of account</em> across people &mdash; or it fails at all three. This is the philosophical bedrock. No interactivity yet, just cold logic that makes every later page land harder.</p>
          <p class="sh-step-payoff"><span class="sh-payoff-label">After this you'll know</span> &mdash; the three jobs every money must do, and why most things called "money" fail at one or more.</p>
          <a href="/what-money-has-to-be.html" class="sh-step-cta">Begin step 1 &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </li>

